wayland-protocols: wayland (Wayland Compositor Infrastructure)
wayland-protocols:
wayland-protocols: Wayland is a protocol for a compositor to talk to its clients as well
wayland-protocols: as a C library implementation of that protocol. The compositor can be
wayland-protocols: a standalone display server running on Linux kernel modesetting and
wayland-protocols: evdev input devices, an X application, or a wayland client itself. The
wayland-protocols: clients can be traditional applications, X servers (rootless or
wayland-protocols: fullscreen) or other display servers.
wayland-protocols:
wayland-protocols: http://wayland.freedesktop.org/
